# Jenkins service-account credentials.
#
# Copy this file to ".env" (same folder) and fill in the values.  One
# pair is enough — the same service account has read access across every
# Jenkins environment the dashboard talks to.  .env is gitignored —
# never commit real credentials.
#
# Get the API key from Jenkins:  your profile  →  Configure  →  API Token.

JENKINS_TEST_USERNAME=
JENKINS_TEST_API_KEY=


# ---
# Optional — fetch concurrency.
#
# JENKINS_MAX_WORKERS controls how many Jenkins API calls run in parallel
# during a Fetch / Refresh.  Defaults to 24 (good for most setups).
# Raise on a beefy Jenkins master (40-50 fine, hard cap 64).
# Lower if you see 429/503 rate-limits or the Jenkins box is under pressure.
#
# JENKINS_POLL_WORKERS is the smaller cap used by the background auto-refresh
# poll (status-only, no console fetch).  Defaults to 15, hard cap 32.
# Kept separate from the main knob because polling shouldn't drown out
# user-triggered fetches.
# ---
# JENKINS_MAX_WORKERS=40
# JENKINS_POLL_WORKERS=15
